# Stable symlink for the keyd virtual keyboard.
# keyd ([ids] *) grabs all physical keyboards and re-emits remapped events through
# this single virtual device. styx captures it (instead of a physical keyboard, which
# keyd holds grabbed) to forward typing to the receiver. The kernel event number
# (eventN) can shift across reboots, so pin a fixed path here: /dev/input/keyd-virtual
SUBSYSTEM=="input", KERNEL=="event*", ATTRS{name}=="keyd virtual keyboard", SYMLINK+="input/keyd-virtual"
